Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
predict_floorplan(25.10)                              predict_floorplan(25.10)

Name
       predict_floorplan  - Generates an initial floorplan that can be used as
       a starting point for making the final floorplan

Syntax
       predict_floorplan

       [-help]

       [-allow_illegal_macro]

       [-enable_cpg]

       [-reshape [[-post_reshape_tcl <string>]]]

       [{-reshape | -skip_generate_fence }]

       Generates an initial floorplan that can be used as a starting point for
       making the final floorplan. It can generates fences  on  power  domains
       automatically,  and  then  does the placement for all instances. If the
       design has macros/blocks, the predict_floorplan command calls the mixed
       placer to place the macros/stdcells, however, the design has only  std-
       cells, then the place_opt_design command is called.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each predict_floorplan parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man predict_floorplan

       -allow_illegal_macro
              Allows  the  tool  to  continue even when macros are not legally
              placed.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -enable_cpg
              Enables CPG for a design which  already  has  a  floorplan  with
              macro locations.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -post_reshape_tcl <string>
              When  specified it allows the tool to load user specified floor-
              plan objects (like tracks) after  the  floorplan  has  been  re-
              shaped.

              Note: This option must be use with the -reshape parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reshape
              Enables  the  floorplan  to  be enlarged in order to fit all in-
              stances.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -skip_generate_fence
              When specified, auto-fence generation is skipped.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

